title: Zoom Enters an Awkward Phase
sub_head: Loss of Five9 deal raises questions about future expansion options as growth keeps slowing
body:
Zoom better enjoy life on its own.
The videoconferencing star walked away from its first major acquisition attempt Thursday. Shareholders for Five9 voted down Zoom Video Communications â€™ proposed all-stock deal, which had drawn opposition from shareholder advisory firms ISS and Glass Lewis over the price.
